&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking for something a little different?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you thought about working within prison healthcare?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are looking for a challenging and rewarding Pharmacy Technician role and want to develop your skills in an environment where no two days are the same then this could be the job for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Pharmacy Technician at HMP Leyhill you will assist in the delivery of a high quality medicines management service to the prison population within a dynamic, friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for dispensing medicines to agreed standards, providing pharmacy related information to patients, whilst also counselling of patients on the correct use of medication. You’ll also help deliver minor ailments services, health bar, serve as a key point of advice to patients in regards to medicines management, help manage the prison’s medicine supplies, and help with medicines reconciliation and supporting patients with their prescription pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through all of this, you’ll serve as a vital point of contact for patients in HMP Leyhill – you’ll empower the prison’s population to understand their medicines better and critically manage their own self-care in regards to their long-term health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn’t a job for everyone. You’ll need to be non-judgemental, resilient, and dedicated. In return you’ll be rewarded through being part of a wider healthcare team that delivers care beyond health - in helping educate your patients to make better life choices, in turn reducing the likelihood of reoffending. This is a real opportunity to gain unique experience and to develop your Pharmacy career to the next level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie Love - Head of Healthcare on 01454 264274 or 07527 292524&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;katie.love@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
